The paper proposes a method for representing the state using natural language, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of reinforcement learning (cs.AI) and compares the performance of language-based agents with vision-based agents (cs.CV). The empirical evidence presented in the paper suggests that the language-based agents are more robust and perform better, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE).
